<paragraph id="8B9336C3BE3CFA7FFF553DD2FAB3F959" blockId="0.[136,1452,1498,1664]" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFF553DD2FF27FA2B" bold="true" box="[136,200,1498,1522]" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">Notes</emphasis>
:—The combination of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3CFA7FFE1C3DD2FD0DFA2B" authority="Cogn." authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1913" box="[449,738,1498,1522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFE1C3DD2FD74FA2B" box="[449,667,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">Tibouchina alpestris</emphasis>
Cogn.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3CFA7FFCDE3DD2FC7BFA2B" authorityName="Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[771,916,1498,1522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Chaetogastra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFCDE3DD2FC7BFA2B" box="[771,916,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">Chaetogastra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is blocked by 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3CFA7FFBF03DD2FA47FA2B" authority="(DC.) Mart." authorityName="Mart." baseAuthorityName="DC." box="[1069,1448,1498,1522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Chaetogastra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFBF03DD2FACEFA2B" box="[1069,1313,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">Chaetogastra alpestris</emphasis>
(DC.) Mart.
</taxonomicName>
, which led 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B32BE3CFA7FFF213DF5FDEFF9CF" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F. &amp; Michelangeli F. A. &amp; Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R." box="[252,512,1533,1558]" pageId="0" pageNumber="94" pagination="937 - 1002" refId="ref2118" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F., Michelangeli F. A., Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R. (2019) Systematics of Tibouchina and allies (Melastomataceae: Melastomateae): a new taxonomic classification. Taxon 68: 937 - 1002. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12151" type="journal article" year="2019">
Guimarães 
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFEA53DF6FE5FF9CC" box="[376,432,1533,1557]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
to create the new name 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D40BE3CFA7FFCCC3DF5FBE7F9CC" box="[785,1032,1533,1557]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Chaetogastra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFCCC3DF5FBE7F9CC" box="[785,1032,1533,1557]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">Chaetogastra montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this taxon. However, according to Article 11.4 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B32BE3CFA7FFE4F3E29FD89F9E0" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[402,614,1569,1593]" pageId="0" pageNumber="94" refId="ref2460" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B958EAD1BE3CFA7FFE323E29FDC9F9E0" box="[495,550,1569,1593]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="94">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), if there is an available name in a more recent synonym “the correct name is the combination of the final epithet of the heterotypic synonym based on the next earliest legitimate name of the taxon at the same rank.” Consequently, no new name was required but a new combination based on the next available synonym.
</paragraph>
